    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the vegetables have started to soften, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>ginger</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> and cook for 30 secs, stirring to coat the vegetables in the flour</p><p>Add 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[250ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> with your <strong>mirin</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong> and 1 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until thickened</p>",
